    {
      "para_id": "Q001497.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Ninĝirsu , the powerful warrior of Enlil , his master , Gudea , ruler of Lagaš , mined this ( piece of ) alabaster in the mountain range of Uringiriaz at the Upper Sea , transported it from there , and fashioned a mace with three lion heads from it . He dedicated it for his well-being to ( Ninĝirsu ) ."
    }
  ],
